<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n41020c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41020c">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41020c"> 20(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> her majority / her minority / man sues the / woman</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Even if an infant <font color="green">[i.e. a person under 21 years of age]</font> has ratified such a promise <font color="green">[of marriage]</font> after coming of age, he or she cannot be sued upon it <font color="green">[breach]</font>; but if, after attaining his or her <mark>majority</mark>, he or she makes a new promise, an action will lie on the new contract. <small> Maud I. Crofts, <a name="MICW" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#MICW"><cite title="source">Women under English Law</cite></a>, 1st ed. (1925) 15</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
